nister is to represent India and its government in the international community. The Foreign Minister also plays an important role in determining [[Indian foreign policy]]. Occasionally, the Foreign Minister is assisted by a Minister of State for External Affairs or the lower-ranked Deputy Minister of External Affairs.\n\nIndia's first Prime Minister, [[Jawaharlal Nehru]], also held the Foreign Minister post throughout his 17-year premiership of the country; he remains the country's longest-serving Foreign Minister. Several other Prime Ministers have since held the additional charge of foreign minister, but never has any other cabinet minister held additional charge of the office. There have been a number of Foreign Ministers who went on to become the Prime Minister like [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]], [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]] and [[I. K. Gujral]].\n\nThe current Minister of External Affairs is [[Subrahmanyam Jaishankar]], succeeding [[Sushma Swaraj]] of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] on 30 May 2019\n\n==List of Foreign Ministers==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:70%;\"\n|-\n!\u2116\n! Name\n! width=75|Portrait\n! colspan=\"2\"|Term of office\n! colspan=\"2\"|Political party<br /><small>(Alliance)</small>\n! Prime Minister\n|- style=\"text-align:center; text-align:center;\"\n|1\n| [[Jawaharlal Nehru]]\n| [[File:Jnehru.jpg|75px]]\n| 2 September 1946\n| 27 May 1964\n| rowspan=\"9\"| [[Indian National Congress]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\" rowspan=9|\n| Himself\n|- align=center\n|2\n| [[Gulzarilal Nanda]]\n| <!-- Commented out: [[File:Gulzarilal Nanda.jpg|75px]] -->\n| 27 May 1964\n| 9 June 1964\n| Himself<br />(acting)\n|- align=center\n|3\n| [[Lal Bahadur Shastri]]\n| [[File:Lal Bahadur Shastri 1966 stamp of India.jpg|75px]]\n| 9 June 1964\n| 17 July 1964\n| Himself\n|- align=center\n|4\n| [[Swaran Singh]]\n|\n| 18 July 1964\n| 14 November 1966\n| [[Lal Bahadur Shastri]]<br />[[Indira Gandhi]]\n|- align=center\n|5\n| [[M. C. Chagla]]\n| [[File:Mohamed Ali Currim Chagla.jpg |75px]]\n| 14 November 1966\n| 5 September 1967\n| rowspan=\"5\"| [[Indira Gandhi]]\n|- align=center\n|6\n| [[Indira Gandhi]]\n| [[File:Indira Gandhi 1977.jpg|75px]]\n| 6 September 1967\n| 13 February 1969\n|- align=center\n|7\n| [[Dinesh Singh (Uttar Pradesh politician)|Dinesh Singh]]\n|\n| 14 February 1969\n| 27 June 1970\n|- align=center\n|(4)\n| [[Sardar Swaran Singh|Swaran Singh]]\n|\n| 27 June 1970\n| 10 October 1974\n|- align=center\n|8\n| [[Yashwantrao Chavan]]\n|\n| 10 October 1974\n| 24 March 1977\n|- align=center\n|9\n| [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee]]\n| [[File:The Prime Minister Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee delivering his speech at the 12th SAARC Summit in Islamabad, Pakistan on January 4, 2004 (1) (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n| 26 March 1977\n| 28 July 1979\n| [[Janata Party]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Janata Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Morarji Desai]]\n|- align=center\n|10\n| [[Shyam Nandan Prasad Mishra]]\n|\n| 28 July 1979\n| 13 January 1980\n| [[Janata Party (Secular)]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Janata Party (Secular)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Charan Singh]]\n|- align=center\n|11\n| [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]]\n| [[File:Pumapaparti.N.rao.jpg|75px]]\n| 14 January 1980\n| 19 July 1984\n|rowspan=\"8\"| [[Indian National Congress]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\" rowspan=8|\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Indira Gandhi]]\n|- align=center\n|(6)\n| [[Indira Gandhi]]\n| [[File:Indira Gandhi 1977.jpg|75px]]\n| 19 July 1984\n| 31 October 1984\n|- align=center\n|12\n| [[Rajiv Gandhi]]\n| [[File:Rajiv Gandhi (1987).jpg|75px]]\n| 31 October 1984\n| 24 September 1985\n| rowspan=\"6\"| [[Rajiv Gandhi]]\n|- align=center\n|13\n| [[Bali Ram Bhagat]]\n| [[File:Nicolae Ceau\u015fescu and B.R. Bhagat (cropped).png|75px]]\n| 25 September 1985\n| 12 May 1986\n|- align=center\n|14\n| [[P. Shiv Shankar]]\n|\n| 12 May 1986\n| 22 October 1986\n|- align=center\n|15\n| [[N. D. Tiwari]]\n| [[File:Ex Uttarakhand CM ND Tiwari.jpg|75px]]\n| 22 October 1986\n| 25 July 1987\n|- align=center\n|(12)\n| [[Rajiv Gandhi]]\n| [[File:Rajiv Gandhi (1987).jpg|75px]]\n| 25 July 1987\n| 25 June 1988\n|- align=center\n|(11)\n| [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]]\n| [[File:Pumapaparti.N.rao.jpg|75px]]\n| 25 June 1988\n| 2 December 1989\n|- align=center\n|16\n| [[V. P. Singh]]\n| [[File:V. P. Singh (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n| 2 December 1989\n| 5 December 1989\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Janata Dal]]<br /><small>([[National Front (India)|National Front]])</small>\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Janata Dal/meta/color}}\" rowspan=2|\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[V. P. Singh]]\n|- align=center\n|17\n| [[I. K. Gujral]]\n| [[File:Inder Kumar Gujral 071.jpg|75px]]\n| 5 December 1989\n| 10 November 1990\n|- align=center\n|18\n| [[Vidya Charan Shukla]]\n|\n| 21 November 1990\n| 20 February 1991\n|rowspan=2| [[Samajwadi Janata Party (Rashtriya)|Samajwadi Janata Party]]<br /><small>\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Samajwadi Janata Party (Rashtriya)/meta/color}}\" rowspan=2 |\n| rowspan=2|[[Chandra Shekhar]]\n|- align=center\n|19\n| [[Chandra Shekhar]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eparlib.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/759802/1/Council_of_Ministers_English.pdf|title=Council of Ministers}}</ref>\n|\n| 20 February 1991\n| 21 June 1991\n|- align=center\n|20\n| [[Madhavsinh Solanki]]\n|\n| 21 June 1991\n| 31 March 1992\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Indian National Congress]]\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\" rowspan=4|\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]]\n|- align=center\n|(11)\n| [[P. V. Narasimha Rao]]\n| [[File:Pumapaparti.N.rao.jpg|75px]]\n| 31 March 1992\n| 18 January 1993\n|- align=center\n|(7)\n| [[Dinesh Singh (Uttar Pradesh politician)|Dinesh Singh]]\n|\n| 18 January 1993\n| 10 February 1995\n|- align=center\n|21\n| [[Pranab Mukherjee]]\n| [[File:Pranab Mukherjee-World Economic Forum Annual Meeting Davos 2009 crop(2).jpg|75px]]\n| 10 February 1995\n| 16 May 1996\n|- align=center\n|22\n| [[Sikander Bakht]]\n|\n| 21 May 1996\n| 