ab Mukherjee-World Economic Forum Annual Meeting Davos 2009 crop(2).jpg|75px]]\n| 24 October 2006<ref name=\"The Hindu\">[http://www.hindu.com/2006/10/25/stories/2006102507670100.htm The Hindu] ''dated'' 25 October 2006, ''accessed'' 25 October 2006. </ref>\n| 22 May 2009\n|- align=center\n|27\n| [[S. M. Krishna]]\n| [[File:India-eam-krishna (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n| 22 May 2009\n| 26 October 2012\n|- align=center\n|28\n| [[Salman Khurshid]]\n| [[File:Salman-kurshid.jpg|75px]]\n| 28 October 2012\n| 26 May 2014\n|- align=center\n|29\n| [[Sushma Swaraj]]\n| [[File:Sushma Swaraj in 2014.jpg|75px]]\n| 26 May 2014\n| 30 May 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]<br /><small>([[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]])</small>\n|width=\"4px\" bgcolor=\"{{Bharatiya Janata Party/meta/color}}\"  rowspan=2|\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Narendra Modi]]\n|- align=center\n|30\n|[[Subrahmanyam Jaishankar]]\n|[[File:Minister Jaishankar (48823162971) (cropped).jpg|75px]]\n|30 May 2019\n|Incumbent\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Foreign Secretary (India)|Indian Foreign Secretary]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://meaindia.nic.in/ Official Website of Ministry of External Affairs]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20040207095317/http://mealib.nic.in/html/forgmin/formins.htm MEA Library]\n\n{{External Affairs Ministers of India}}\n{{Heads of the Ministries of the Government of India}}\n{{Foreign relations of India}}\n\n[[Category:Union ministers of India]]\n[[Category:Ministers for External Affairs of India]]\n[[Category:Foreign ministers]]\n[[Category:Ministry of External Affairs (India)]]\n[[Category:Lists of government ministers of India]]\n{{DEFAULTSORT:External_Affairs_(India) Minister}}\n", "name_user": "Fylindfotberserk", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript, EngvarB", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minister_of_External_Affairs_(India)"}
{"title_page": "Christus, der uns selig macht", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical composition\n| name                = \"{{Lang|de|Christus, der uns selig macht|italic=no}}\"\n| type                = [[Lutheran hymn]]\n| composer            = \n| image               = Christus, der uns selig macht (BWV 245.15).jpg\n| image_upright       = 1.6\n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Bach's setting of the hymn in [[St John Passion structure#15|his ''St John Passion'']]\n| Title_English       = {{nowrap|\"Christ who hath us blessed made\"}}\n| occasion            = [[Passion music|Passion]]\n| text                = [[Michael Wei\u00dfe]]\n| language            = German\n| melody              = [[Bohemian Brethren]]\n| composed            = 1501\n| published           = {{plainlist|\n* {{Start date|1531}}\n}}\n}}\n'''\"{{Lang|de|Christus, der uns selig macht|italic=no}}\"''' (literally: Christ who makes us blessed) is a German Lutheran [[Passion music|Passion hymn]] in eight stanzas in German by [[Michael Wei\u00dfe]], written in 1531 as a translation of the Latin hymn \"Patris Sapientia\" to an older melody of the [[Bohemian Brethren]]. \n\nThe hymn inspired musical settings, both vocal and for organ, notably Bach's ''[[St John Passion structure|St John Passion]]'', where the first and last [[stanza]]s comment on biblical scenes in two different settings. The hymn is part of the Protestant hymnal as EG 77. It was translated to \"Christ, by whose all-saving Light\" and other versions.\n\n== History ==\nWei\u00dfe wrote the text as a translation of the Latin hymn \"Patris Sapientia\", attributed to Aegidius of Collonna,<ref name=\"Hymnology\" /> from the [[Liturgy of the Hours]] for [[Good Friday]].<ref name=\"BCW\" /> The text of the Latin hymn follows the seven station hours in Christ's suffering that day, and relates to the [[canonical hours]] from [[Matins]] to [[Compline]]. Wei\u00dfe added an eighth stanza as a summary.<ref name=\"BCW\" /> Each of the seven translated stanzas narrates a situation of the Passion, beginning with Jesus being arrested \"like a thief\" (\"als ein Dieb\") in the early morning hours; the final stanza is a prayer, \"O hilf, Christ, Gottes Sohn\" (O help, Christ, God's Son), requesting help to commemorate the Passion fruitfully (\"fruchtbarlich\"), to remain faithful to Jesus and avoid all wrongdoing, and to give thanks.<ref name=\"Hymnology\" />\n\nWei\u00dfe published his text in 1531 in his hymnal {{Lang|de|Ein New Gesengbuchlen}} for the [[Bohemian Brethren]],<ref name=\"Hymnology\" /> with a melody known from the beginning of the 15th century and used in Czech congregations in Bohemian [[Hussite]] hymnals.<ref name=\"BCW\" /><ref name=\"Hymnary tune\" />\n\nIn the current German Protestant hymnal {{lang|de|[[Evangelisches Gesangbuch]]}} (EG), the hymn is number 77,<ref name=\"Bremen\" /> appearing in all eight stanzas with only slight changes.<ref name=\"Hymnology\" /> The hymn was translated to English in several versions,<ref name=\"Hymnary\" /> for example \"Christ, by whose all-saving Light\" by Johann Christian Jacobi.<ref name=\"Hymnary en\" />\n\n== Text and tune ==\n\nThe first stanza, as harmonized by Johann Sebastian Bach in his ''[[St John Passion structure|St John Passion]]'', goes as follows:{{efn|Translation: Christ, who makes us blessed / and has done no wrong, / was for us in the night / seized like a thief, / led before godless people / and falsely accused, / derided, mocked and spat upon, / as the scripture says.<!--translation from CPDL-->}}\n<score vorbis=\"1\">\n<< <<\n\\new Staff { \\clef treble \\time 4/4 \\key a \\minor \\set Staff.midiInstrument = \"flute\" \\relative c'' \n  << { \n  \\set Score.tempoHideNote = ##t \\override Score.BarNumber  #'transparent = ##t\n  e4 e e e | d c b2\\fermata | c4 d e e | d ( c4 ) b2\\fermata | \n  a4 b c a | a8 g f4 e2\\fermata | f4 g a a | g ( f4 ) e2\\fermata |\n  a4 gis a b | c b a2\\fermata | c4 d e e | d ( c4 ) b2\\fermata |\n  a4 b c a | a8 g f4 e2\\fermata | f4 g a a | g ( f4 ) e2~ | e1\\fermata \\bar \"|.\" } \\\\ \n  { gis4 gis a b | a a gis2 | e8 fis g4 g f8 e | f4 ( e4 ) e2 |\n  e4 e e f | e d cis2 | d4 e es d | d2 cis | \n  d4 e e fis8 gis? | a4 g! fis2 | g4 g g f! | f ( e8 fis ) g2 \n  a4 e e e | a, d cis2 | d4 e f f | e ( d2 c4 ) | b1 } \n  >>\n}\n\\new Lyrics \\lyricmode {\nChri4 -- stus, der uns se -- lig macht,2\nkein4 B\u00f6s hat be -- gan2 -- gen,\nder4 ward f\u00fcr uns in der Nacht,2\nals4 ein Dieb ge -- fan2 -- gen,\nge4 -- f\u00fchrt vor gott -- lo -- se Leut,2\nund4 f\u00e4lsch -- lich ver -- kla2 -- get,\nver4 -- lacht, ver -- h\u00f6hnt und ver -- speit,2\nwie4 denn die Schrift sa2 -- get.\n}\n\\new Staff { \\clef bass \\key a \\minor \\set Staff.midiInstrument = \"flute\" \\relative c'\n  << { b4 b c b8 c | d e f4 b,2 | a4 bes bes a | a2 gis |\n  c4 b a8 b c d | e4 a, a2 | a4 c c c | bes8 ( c8 d4 ) a2 |\n  a4 b! c d | e d d2 | c4 bes a a | a8 b! c4 d2 |\n  d8 c b4 a8 b c d | e4 a, a2 | a4 c c c | c8 ( b8 a4 gis a ) | gis1 } \\\\ \n  { e4 e a g | f e8 d e2 | a4 g cis, cis | d ( a4 ) e'2 |\n  a4 gis a f | cis d a2 | d4 c f, fis | g ( gis4 ) a2 | \n  f'4 e8 d c4 b | a4 b8 c d2 | es4 d cis d8 e! | f ( g8 a4 ) g2 | \n  fis4 gis a a,8 b | cis4 d a2 | d4 c! f,8 g a b | c4 ( d4 ) e2~ | e1 } \n  >>\n}\n>> >>\n\\layout { indent = #0 }\n\\midi { \\tempo 4 = 80 }\n</score>\n\n== Music ==\nIn his ''[[St John Passion structure|St John Passion]]'', Bach used two stanzas: the second part opens with the first stanza, \"{{lang|de|Christus, der uns selig macht|italic=no}}\" (Christ, who hath us blessed made), which summarises what Jesus had to endure although innocent (\"made captive, ... falsely indicted, and mocked and scorned and bespat\"),<ref>[https://www.bach-digital.de/receive/BachDigitalWork_work_00011274 Christus, der uns selig macht BWV 245/15 ChS; BC F 31.2 / Chorale] [[Bach Digital]]</ref><ref>Luke Dahn: [http://www.bach-chorales.com/BWV0245_15.htm BWV 245.15] bach-chorales.com</ref> while the scene of the Crucifixion ends with the final stanza, \"{{lang|de|O hilf, Christe, Gottes Sohn|italic=no}}\" (O help, Christ, O Son of God).<ref>Luke Dahn: [http://www.bach-chorales.com/BWV0245_37.htm BWV 245.37] bach-chorales.com</ref> Bach also wrote a [[chorale prelude]] on the hymn, BWV 747.<ref>{{IMSLP|work=Christus, der uns selig macht, BWV 747 (Bach, Johann Sebastian)|cname=Christus, der uns selig macht, BWV 747 (Bach, Johann Sebastian)}}</ref>\n\nSeven of the eight stanzas are used in the mid-18th century [[pasticcio]] [[Passion oratorio]] ''[[Wer ist der, so von Edom k\u00f6mmt]]'' in movements 2, 24, 27, 30, 38, 40 and 42.<ref name=\"Altnikol\">{{IMSLP|work=Wer ist der, so von Edom k\u00f6mmt (Altnikol, Johann Christoph)|cname=Wer ist der, so von Edom k\u00f6mmt (Altnikol, Johann Christoph)}}</ref> [[Mauricio Kagel]] quoted the hymn, paraphrased to \"Bach, der uns selig macht\", in his oratorio ''[[Sankt-Bach-Passion]]'' about Bach's life, composed for the tricentenary of Bach's birth in 1985.<ref name=\"Prestoclassical\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist | 30em\n| refs =\n\n<ref name=\"Bremen\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.l4a.org/cgi-bin/4lieder?lookupMode=liedaufschlagen&lookup=Evangelisches%20Gesangbuch+77\n| title = 4Bibeln: Gesangbuch / Evangelisches Gesangbuch 77\n| website = Evangelisches Gesangbuch / Niedersachsen \u2013 Bremen\n| language = de\n| accessdate = 11 April 2019\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"BCW\">{{cite web\n| url = http://www.bach-cantatas.com/Texts/Chorale155-Eng3.htm\n| title = Chorale Texts used in Bach's Vocal Works / Christus der uns selig macht / Text and Translation of Chorale\n| website = Bach Cantatas Website\n| accessdate = 6 April 2019\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Hymnary\">{{cite web\n| url = https://hymnary.org/text/christus_der_uns_selig_macht_kein\n| title = Christus, der uns selig macht\n| website = hymnary.org\n| accessdate = 6 April 2019\n}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Hymnary tune\">{{cite web\n| url = ht